#week-title("One", "The Qabalah & The Tree of Life")

=== Core Teaching

The *Qabalah* (specifically the Hermetic Qabalah) is the philosophical and
symbolic skeleton underlying the Tarot, astrology, alchemy, and the magical arts.
Its central diagram is the *Tree of Life*: ten spheres (sephiroth) and
twenty-two connecting pathways arranged in a specific pattern that maps all of
existence from the most subtle spiritual reality (Kether — the Crown) to the
densest material expression (Malkuth — the Kingdom).

The Tree is simultaneously a map of the cosmos and a map of the human being. As
Oliver St. John states plainly: "The Tree of Life represents man and the
universe, microcosm and macrocosm."

#doctrine[
  _"The alchemical student benefits from approaching the Tree not as abstract
  metaphysics but as a living filing system: every plant, metal, planet,
  operation, and inner state has its place on the Tree."_
